results.name: Number of strict integer partitions of n into Fermi-Dirac primes.
comment: A Fermi-Dirac prime (A050376) is a number of the form p^(2^k) where p is prime and k >= 0.
formula: O.g.f.: Product_d (1 + x^d) where the product is over all Fermi-Dirac primes (A050376).
example: The a(16) = 9 strict integer partitions of 16 into Fermi-Dirac primes:
